<item>
            <title>[HBASE-12021] Hbase shell does not respect the HBASE_OPTS set by the user in console</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-12021</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Before starting hbase shell i have set some -D parameters reauired for kerberos authentication in HBASE_OPTS (there is no other variables are used when shell is executed). But while invoking Hbase shell it is not used.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The code in hbase-env.sh is &lt;br/&gt;
export HBASE_OPTS=&quot;-XX:+UseConcMarkSweepGC&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This will overwrite the the value set in the console&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There can be 2 options to support this&lt;br/&gt;
1. Append the HBASE_OPTS like HBASE_OPTS=&quot;$HBASE_OPTS -XX:+UseConcMarkSweepGC&quot;.&lt;br/&gt;
2. Have a new variable (HBASE_CLIENT_OPTS) which is can be appended in shell section of &quot;hbase&quot; file&lt;/p&gt;</description>
